She's busy during the day.

574
00:30:50,204 --> 00:30:51,648
She has no time at night either.

575
00:30:56,780 --> 00:30:58,020
Xin is really

576
00:30:58,220 --> 00:30:59,460
capable now.

577
00:30:59,660 --> 00:31:01,260
Her show has even gone international.

578
00:31:02,315 --> 00:31:03,382
When will it be on air?

579
00:31:03,460 --> 00:31:04,860
Where can I watch it?

580
00:31:12,860 --> 00:31:13,610
What's going on?

581
00:31:14,980 --> 00:31:16,420
You've been quiet all evening.

582
00:31:19,300 --> 00:31:21,780
Did you and Wu Si have a fight?

583
00:31:27,380 --> 00:31:27,940
No.

584
00:31:28,740 --> 00:31:30,500
Maybe she's just tired from work.

585
00:31:32,580 --> 00:31:34,140
If you're tired, eat more.

586
00:31:40,620 --> 00:31:42,026
- Okay.
- Here, Captain.

587
00:31:44,460 --> 00:31:45,420
- Mrs. Tang.
- Eat up.

588
00:31:52,780 --> 00:31:54,500
Well, the fruit...

589
00:32:01,380 --> 00:32:01,780
Here.

590
00:32:02,340 --> 00:32:02,900
Wu Si.

591
00:32:03,420 --> 00:32:06,300
Xin has always been hot-tempered.

592
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:09,248
Sometimes, don't take it to heart.

593
00:32:09,540 --> 00:32:11,340
But you can't spoil

594
00:32:12,580 --> 00:32:13,100
women.

595
00:32:14,940 --> 00:32:16,580
Captain, it's okay.

596
00:32:17,380 --> 00:32:18,540
I trust Tang Xin

597
00:32:18,780 --> 00:32:19,660
is reasonable

598
00:32:20,020 --> 00:32:21,540
and sensible.

599
00:32:29,820 --> 00:32:30,620
Good.

600
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:37,740
Time for our daily walk.

601
00:32:38,340 --> 00:32:40,020
My wife and I never miss it.

602
00:32:40,020 --> 00:32:41,700
Yes, let's go walk. Let's go.

603
00:32:41,900 --> 00:32:43,300
Sit down. No need to be formal.

604
00:33:17,210 --> 00:33:17,860
Let me ask you.

605
00:33:19,500 --> 00:33:20,860
Did you talk to my dad earlier?

606
00:33:21,060 --> 00:33:21,620
I didn't.

607
00:33:22,630 --> 00:33:23,340
I said nothing.

608
00:33:23,471 --> 00:33:25,182
No? Then why did he
ask me that just now?

609
00:33:25,820 --> 00:33:26,500
With Captain...

610
00:33:28,180 --> 00:33:29,570
With Captain Tang's experience

611
00:33:29,820 --> 00:33:32,060
and your lack of composure,

612
00:33:32,060 --> 00:33:33,100
you gave yourself away.

613
00:33:42,660 --> 00:33:44,620
I always thought
Miss Tang was experienced

614
00:33:45,260 --> 00:33:46,300
and mentally strong.

615
00:33:46,980 --> 00:33:47,780
Who knew

616
00:33:48,260 --> 00:33:49,500
that's not the truth.

617
00:33:50,220 --> 00:33:51,340
You only take praise

618
00:33:51,980 --> 00:33:53,493
and can't handle criticism.

619
00:33:56,980 --> 00:33:57,780
Yes.

620
00:33:58,026 --> 00:33:59,240
I was always a model student.

621
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:00,180
Teachers praised me.

622
00:34:00,180 --> 00:34:01,110
No one criticized me.

623
00:34:01,693 --> 00:34:02,620
What about your parents?

624
00:34:02,820 --> 00:34:03,820
They praised me too.

625
00:34:03,820 --> 00:34:05,550
I was showered with praise
since childhood.

626
00:34:05,820 --> 00:34:07,160
Now I know the problem.

627
00:34:09,340 --> 00:34:11,100
I realize my mistake, Miss Tang.

628
00:34:11,340 --> 00:34:12,100
From now on,

629
00:34:12,740 --> 00:34:14,500
I'll talk to you differently.

630
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:15,100
No need.

631
00:34:16,720 --> 00:34:17,360
Don't bother.

632
00:34:23,826 --> 00:34:24,715
Suit yourself.

633
00:34:35,248 --> 00:34:36,493
Let me help you carry that.

634
00:34:36,500 --> 00:34:37,860
No, I've got it.

635
00:34:38,060 --> 00:34:39,260
I brought some materials.

636
00:34:39,700 --> 00:34:41,060
Thank you very much.

637
00:34:41,540 --> 00:34:42,940
I feel a bit bad.

638
00:34:43,140 --> 00:34:44,350
Wang Chen is still in hospital.

639
00:34:44,350 --> 00:34:45,300
She still needs care,

640
00:34:45,300 --> 00:34:46,900
yet I asked you to come here.

641
00:34:47,100 --> 00:34:48,820
I can't do much there anyway.

642
00:34:49,300 --> 00:34:50,900
Alright, I won't hold back.

643
00:34:50,900 --> 00:34:52,137
Let's go to the meeting room.

644
00:34:52,300 --> 00:34:54,220
Sure. I'll follow your lead here.

645
00:34:54,420 --> 00:34:54,820
Great.

646
00:34:56,382 --> 00:34:58,204
(Minghua News)
During the Song Dynasty,

647
00:34:58,700 --> 00:34:59,770
the compass

648
00:34:59,770 --> 00:35:01,810
was applied to navigation.

649
00:35:02,380 --> 00:35:04,340
It greatly boosted China's ability

650
00:35:04,540 --> 00:35:05,490
to sail long distances.

651
00:35:06,340 --> 00:35:07,100
The Song Dynasty

652
00:35:07,300 --> 00:35:08,790
also valued commerce

653
00:35:09,140 --> 00:35:10,540
and encouraged maritime trade,

654
00:35:10,990 --> 00:35:12,980
so maritime trade

655
00:35:12,980 --> 00:35:15,180
expanded across
Asia, Africa, and Europe.

656
00:35:15,900 --> 00:35:16,640
No wonder

657
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:19,580
ancient Chinese sunken ships

658
00:35:19,860 --> 00:35:21,260
are found in many foreign waters.

659
00:35:21,620 --> 00:35:22,200
Indeed.

660
00:35:23,340 --> 00:35:24,850
The Maritime Silk Road

661
00:35:24,850 --> 00:35:25,850
has another name.

662
00:35:26,220 --> 00:35:27,420
In 1913,

663
00:35:27,730 --> 00:35:29,890
French sinologist Édouard Chavannes
proposed it.

664
00:35:30,260 --> 00:35:31,820
He called it the Maritime Spice Route

665
00:35:32,060 --> 00:35:33,580
and the Maritime Porcelain Route.

666
00:35:34,620 --> 00:35:36,860
Based
on the Maritime Porcelain Route idea,

667
00:35:37,140 --> 00:35:38,670
ceramics took up

668
00:35:38,670 --> 00:35:41,060
a large proportion of China's exports.

669
00:35:41,260 --> 00:35:43,660
Yes. Ceramics are unlike other goods.

670
00:35:43,860 --> 00:35:45,980
They're highly resistant to corrosion.

671
00:35:46,340 --> 00:35:47,340
That's why

672
00:35:47,382 --> 00:35:49,004
they can be well preserved underwater.

673
00:35:49,380 --> 00:35:50,580
In recent years,

674
00:35:50,780 --> 00:35:52,900
ancient Chinese ceramics
have become very valuable

675
00:35:52,900 --> 00:35:54,100
at auctions.

676
00:35:54,500 --> 00:35:55,620
It's why

677
00:35:56,250 --> 00:35:57,310
antique smugglers

678
00:35:57,310 --> 00:35:58,300
and criminals

679
00:35:58,300 --> 00:36:00,190
have targeted sunken ship relics.

680
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:01,500
Of course,

681
00:36:01,700 --> 00:36:03,500
many sunken ships also contain

682
00:36:03,537 --> 00:36:05,382
many valuable gold, silver, and jewels.

683
00:36:08,780 --> 00:36:09,730
How is Yangyang doing?

684
00:36:12,460 --> 00:36:13,820
She pretty much recovered,

685
00:36:14,293 --> 00:36:15,700
but she's still affected mentally.

686
00:36:18,020 --> 00:36:18,970
It takes time to heal.

687
00:36:19,515 --> 00:36:20,493
It's not your fault.

688
00:36:21,230 --> 00:36:22,280
But as a man,

689
00:36:22,537 --> 00:36:23,782
you must be responsible.

690
00:36:25,737 --> 00:36:27,204
Take good care of Yangyang.

691
00:36:27,900 --> 00:36:29,300
Tell me if you need anything.

692
00:36:32,220 --> 00:36:33,380
I need something right now.

693
00:36:37,060 --> 00:36:37,740
Time me.

694
00:36:44,026 --> 00:36:45,100
How are you feeling today?

695
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:48,620
The doctor said
she has started physiotherapy,

696
00:36:48,620 --> 00:36:50,020
and it's going pretty well.

697
00:36:51,460 --> 00:36:52,060
Not enough.

698
00:36:52,915 --> 00:36:53,700
I'm still far off.

699
00:36:54,100 --> 00:36:55,420
That's not up to you.

700
00:36:55,940 --> 00:36:56,980
It's up to the doctor.

701
00:36:57,550 --> 00:36:58,720
I told you last time.

702
00:36:59,060 --> 00:37:00,380
Soldiers follow orders.

703
00:37:00,380 --> 00:37:02,380
Patients follow the doctor's advice.

704
00:37:03,260 --> 00:37:03,940
Understand?

705
00:37:04,580 --> 00:37:05,140
Yes.

706
00:37:05,580 --> 00:37:06,140
Louder.

707
00:37:07,740 --> 00:37:08,380
Yes!

708
00:37:08,860 --> 00:37:09,860
That's more like it.

709
00:37:10,180 --> 00:37:11,660
You were hurt saving someone.

710
00:37:12,180 --> 00:37:13,980
A heroic wound heals faster.

711
00:37:14,740 --> 00:37:15,910
Listen, Blue Blade

712
00:37:15,910 --> 00:37:17,260
is now full of hot-headed kids.

713
00:37:17,380 --> 00:37:18,420
You can't fall behind.

714
00:37:18,750 --> 00:37:19,750
Do what the doctor says.

715
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,760
I'll be expecting
to spar with you next year.

716
00:37:23,004 --> 00:37:24,350
I promise to complete the mission.

717
00:37:24,460 --> 00:37:25,820
Alright, lie down and rest.

718
00:37:28,210 --> 00:37:29,450
I feel relieved seeing you.

719
00:37:29,693 --> 00:37:30,626
By the way, Bai,

720
00:37:31,620 --> 00:37:32,780
tell me immediately

721
00:37:32,780 --> 00:37:34,093
if she doesn't follow orders.

722
00:37:34,420 --> 00:37:36,460
Let's see if she obeys her brigadier.

723
00:37:37,380 --> 00:37:38,660
Alright, great.

724
00:37:39,826 --> 00:37:41,180
I'm leaving. You worked hard.

725
00:37:41,180 --> 00:37:42,450
Thank you, Brigadier. Thank you.

726
00:37:42,450 --> 00:37:43,690
- I'm off.
- Let me walk you out.

727
00:37:43,693 --> 00:37:44,404
No need.

728
00:37:48,100 --> 00:37:48,900
I figured it out.

729
00:37:49,380 --> 00:37:50,600
Only Brigadier can handle you.

730
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:52,900
Didn't I say the same things?

731
00:37:53,660 --> 00:37:54,960
Why won't you listen to me?

732
00:37:55,380 --> 00:37:56,220
You even saluted.

733
00:37:56,740 --> 00:37:57,982
You never saluted me.

734
00:39:04,660 --> 00:39:05,380
How long?

735
00:39:06,782 --> 00:39:07,540
I didn't time it.

736
00:39:12,500 --> 00:39:13,420
It must be

737
00:39:13,715 --> 00:39:15,137
at least four and a half minutes.

738
00:39:18,460 --> 00:39:19,060
Feeling better?

739
00:39:23,500 --> 00:39:23,940
Captain.

740
00:39:28,648 --> 00:39:29,780
It hurts inside.

741
00:39:37,860 --> 00:39:38,460
Zong Qing.

742
00:39:39,380 --> 00:39:39,980
I...

743
00:39:41,315 --> 00:39:42,820
I don't know how to comfort you.

744
00:39:43,500 --> 00:39:45,180
If it were me in your shoes,

745
00:39:45,740 --> 00:39:47,780
no one could comfort me either.

746
00:39:48,980 --> 00:39:49,540
But

747
00:39:50,580 --> 00:39:52,540
just say the word

748
00:39:52,848 --> 00:39:54,426
if you ever need help.

749
00:39:55,060 --> 00:39:55,620
I'm here.

750
00:40:02,020 --> 00:40:02,580
Captain.

751
00:40:11,140 --> 00:40:11,780
You know what?

752
00:40:12,537 --> 00:40:14,930
I've had this scene
stuck in my head for the past two days.

753
00:40:18,010 --> 00:40:19,090
It's when I called Yangyang

754
00:40:19,090 --> 00:40:20,420
back on the ship.

755
00:40:27,570 --> 00:40:29,000
Just to get Yangyang to eat well.

756
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:30,940
I told the baby

757
00:40:31,740 --> 00:40:32,700
on the phone

758
00:40:34,300 --> 00:40:35,100
not to bully Mom

759
00:40:35,740 --> 00:40:36,940
and let her eat well.

760
00:40:38,780 --> 00:40:40,540
I was so loud.

761
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:47,537
The first and last things

762
00:40:49,900 --> 00:40:52,060
the baby heard from me

763
00:40:56,740 --> 00:40:57,820
were fierce.

764
00:41:01,540 --> 00:41:02,500
Do you think

765
00:41:02,500 --> 00:41:03,493
I'm the worst dad ever?

766
00:41:08,915 --> 00:41:10,620
Yangyang and the baby did nothing wrong.

767
00:41:10,620 --> 00:41:11,582
I'm the one at fault.

768
00:41:15,871 --> 00:41:17,515
I didn't take good care of them.

769
00:41:27,740 --> 00:41:29,300
You two have just started.

770
00:41:29,448 --> 00:41:30,540
There's a long road ahead.

771
00:41:32,020 --> 00:41:32,700
Live well.

772
00:41:33,740 --> 00:41:34,540
It'll get better.

773
00:41:58,940 --> 00:42:02,420
♪The vast sky and sea,
this deep blue expanse♪

774
00:42:03,110 --> 00:42:06,380
♪So deep, so boundless♪

775
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:09,890
♪Just like your arms♪

776
00:42:10,380 --> 00:42:13,500
♪Shielding me from the dark clouds♪

777
00:42:13,790 --> 00:42:17,430
♪Always bearing it all in silence♪

778
00:42:17,430 --> 00:42:23,850
♪Even the long, long road gives me peace
when you're there♪

779
00:42:24,350 --> 00:42:28,750
♪Not one to show romance
in front of others♪

780
00:42:29,210 --> 00:42:32,300
♪You speak of dreams
with such calm simplicity♪

781
00:42:33,090 --> 00:42:37,890
♪But I know your heart
holds much deeper hopes♪

782
00:42:40,160 --> 00:42:42,000
♪I truly understand♪

783
00:42:42,490 --> 00:42:46,680
♪You speak of love so slowly♪

784
00:42:46,930 --> 00:42:52,900
♪But your eyes have already
told me everything♪

785
00:42:53,406 --> 00:42:56,096
♪Using up all my fortune♪

786
00:42:56,100 --> 00:43:00,500
♪Just to trade a lifetime with you♪

787
00:43:00,590 --> 00:43:02,810
♪Thank you for awakening♪

788
00:43:02,820 --> 00:43:07,900
♪The courage once hidden in my fear♪

789
00:43:08,040 --> 00:43:11,230
♪Turning every chance into certainty♪

790
00:43:11,560 --> 00:43:15,090
♪Turning every tie into companionship♪

791
00:43:15,170 --> 00:43:20,140
♪Blooming into brilliance
for all the years to come♪

792
00:43:20,140 --> 00:43:24,130
♪No one can tear us apart♪

793
00:43:24,320 --> 00:43:27,670
♪Each time my palm feels warmth again♪

794
00:43:27,930 --> 00:43:33,270
♪The memories return,
and I'm no longer alone♪

795
00:43:34,160 --> 00:43:38,150
♪No matter how far
across time and space♪

796
00:43:38,400 --> 00:43:41,800
♪My longing reaches you in silence♪

797
00:43:41,920 --> 00:43:46,450
♪No need to call out loudly♪

798
00:43:46,450 --> 00:43:49,120
♪No matter how much it takes♪

799
00:43:49,140 --> 00:43:53,550
♪To bring this drifting heart to shore♪

800
00:43:53,550 --> 00:43:56,810
♪Thank you for standing behind me♪

801
00:43:56,830 --> 00:44:00,880
♪Lighting up the darkness and despair♪

802
00:44:00,880 --> 00:44:04,350
♪The bigger the world,
the lonelier it feels♪

803
00:44:04,350 --> 00:44:08,120
♪Only by your side♪

804
00:44:08,130 --> 00:44:15,210
♪Can I truly feel this warmth inside♪
